<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - A1 - Metadata - Resource provides computational access"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_A1_FS_ProvidesCompAccess"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database, standard or policy resource provides computational access to its content. In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to at least one Data Process that uses an access method other than User Interface and whose process type includes Read or Read/Write. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

A1 requires that (meta)data are retrievable using a standardised communications protocol. Computational access enables integration with software systems, automated workflows, FAIR assessment services, data analysis pipelines and machine-assisted discovery services by allowing content to be retrieved through computational means. This metric is related to FAIR Metric - F4 - Metadata - Resource provides machine search interface, but is deliberately broader in scope. Whereas the F4 metric evaluates whether machines can discover content through search or browse functions, this metric evaluates whether any computational access mechanism is available for retrieving content from the resource. This distinction reflects the focus of FAIR Principle A1 on retrievability rather than discoverability."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/A1> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
